          &lt;p&gt;Where does the end begin? Where does the end end? And what the HELL is happening in the middle?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These are some of the questions we tackle in this episode as we explore Aardvark Weather, an end-to-end forecasting system. End-to-end models are super cool, and likely to be the future of weather forecasting—but they also revitalize old questions about transparency, end-user trust, and the fidelity &amp;amp; availability of raw observations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us as we unpack what an end-to-end model is, the Aardvark Weather approach, and how these models at-large might shape the landscape of forecasting (And books. Always books.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Featured paper&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-025-08897-0#Sec2&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;End-to-end data-driven weather prediction&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Additional reading&lt;/h2&gt;
